    <h1 class="opener__hed  -is-over-bg opener__hed--light opener__hed--small" >        Biden Asked Microsoft to “Raise the Bar on Cybersecurity.” He May Have Helped Create an Illegal Monopoly.
    </h1>

    
            <div class="article-meta-1  -is-over-bg article-meta-1--light">
            <span class="article-meta-1__byline">
                by <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/renee-dudley">Renee Dudley</a>, with research by <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/doris-burke">Doris Burke</a>            </span>
            <time class="article-meta-1__pubdate">
                <time class="timestamp" datetime="2024-11-15EST06:00">Nov. 15, 6 a.m. EST</time>
            </time>
        </div>
    
    </div> <!-- Close .opener__topic-title-dek-wrapper -->

            <div class="content"> <!-- not sure if this is the best way to reestablish the text column -->
            <h2 class="opener__dek opener__dek--match-text-column" style="display: none">                When the White House welcomed Microsoft’s offer of $150 million in tech services, it helped the world’s largest software provider tighten its grip on federal business and freeze out competitors.
            </h2>
        </div>
    
</div>
        
