    </div>

    
    <div class="user-level--2__show user-level--3__show">
        
<div class="lead-in">
            <p class="lead-in__title" id="read-more">Read More</p>
        </div>

    </div>

    
                    
    
                            
        <a href="https://www.propublica.org/article/cyber-safety-board-never-investigated-solarwinds-breach-microsoft" class="story-promo section-articles" >

            
                                                                                                                                
                                    
                    <div class="story-promo__art">
                        <img
                            class="lazyload"
                            alt=""
                            src="data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D%27http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg%27%20width%3D%271%27%20height%3D%271%27%20style%3D%27background%3Atransparent%27%2F%3E"
                            width="75"
                            height="75"
                            data-sizes="auto"
                            data-srcset="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20240416-KAHN-Tech-Project-0210_maxWidth_3000_maxHeight_3000_ppi_72_quality_95_embedColorProfile_true.jpg?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fp-x=0.5281&amp;fp-y=0.5426&amp;h=75&amp;q=70&amp;w=75&amp;s=f9b83a4e96b71a5e2139979dca18f739 75w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20240416-KAHN-Tech-Project-0210_maxWidth_3000_maxHeight_3000_ppi_72_quality_95_embedColorProfile_true.jpg?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fp-x=0.5281&amp;fp-y=0.5426&amp;h=150&amp;q=70&amp;w=150&amp;s=9f5544c7c1b036469268b320c080cad1 150w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20240416-KAHN-Tech-Project-0210_maxWidth_3000_maxHeight_3000_ppi_72_quality_95_embedColorProfile_true.jpg?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fp-x=0.5281&amp;fp-y=0.5426&amp;h=400&amp;q=70&amp;w=400&amp;s=a75510c083b8133d1745ecd14b3b07ce 400w"
                            />
                    </div>
                
            
            <div class="story-promo__info" dir="auto">
                <strong class="story-promo__hed">The President Ordered a Board to Probe a Massive Russian Cyberattack. It Never Did.</strong>
                            </div>
        </a>

    
</aside>
        
    
                    
<p data-pp-blocktype="copy" data-pp-id="111.0">Still, just last year, Chinese hackers exploited Microsoft security lapses to breach the email accounts of senior U.S. officials. Investigating the attack, the federal Cyber Safety Review Board <a href="https://www.cisa.gov/sites/default/files/2024-04/CSRB_Review_of_the_Summer_2023_MEO_Intrusion_Final_508c.pdf">faulted the company</a> for a “cascade of … avoidable errors” and pressed it to overhaul its security culture. Microsoft has since pledged to place security “above all else.” In June, <a href="https://www.propublica.org/article/microsoft-solarwinds-cybersecurity-house-homeland-security-hearing">Smith told Congress</a> that Microsoft would strive to establish a “culture that encourages every employee to look for problems, find problems, report problems, help fix problems and then learn from the problems.”</p>
        
    
                    
<p data-pp-blocktype="copy" data-pp-id="112.0">It’s learning from the successes, too. The same week that Smith testified before Congress, and nearly three years after Nadella made his commitment at Biden’s summit, Microsoft <a href="https://news.microsoft.com/2024/06/10/microsoft-to-help-rural-hospitals-defend-against-rising-cybersecurity-attacks/">made a new offer</a>, this time to “support hospitals serving more than 60 million people living in rural America.”</p>
        
    
                    
<p data-pp-blocktype="copy" data-pp-id="113.0">The playbook was familiar. In its announcement, the company said that eligible hospitals could have the private-sector equivalent of the G5 “<a href="https://nonprofits.tsi.microsoft.com/EN-US/security-program-for-rural-hospitals/">at no cost for one year</a>.” As before, Faehl said Microsoft made the commitment “at the behest of the White House.”</p>
        
    
        
    </div>

    <footer class="article-footer" data-pp-location="article footer">
        
    
